03:58.805 --> 04:01.542
<i>♪♪ And I don't really care</i>
<i>if you think I'm strange</i>

04:01.575 --> 04:03.544
<i>♪♪ I ain't gonna change</i>

04:03.577 --> 04:06.713
<i>♪♪ And I'm never gonna care</i>
<i>'bout my bad reputation</i>

04:07.748 --> 04:08.782
<i>♪♪ Not me! ♪♪</i>

04:11.384 --> 04:13.720
Hey, look! Maplefarm Realty

04:13.754 --> 04:16.156
gave everyone in the
neighborhood free pumpkins!

04:16.189 --> 04:18.191
Wasn't that nice?

04:18.224 --> 04:20.093
Well, there's nothing
nice about it.

04:20.126 --> 04:21.728
It's a cheap way
to get customers.

04:21.762 --> 04:23.263
They give you
a 20‐cent pumpkin,

04:23.296 --> 04:25.031
you give them 10 grand
to sell the house.

04:25.065 --> 04:26.099
Some deal.

04:26.132 --> 04:28.735
Well, I just think
it was nice.

04:28.769 --> 04:29.603
Ooh.

04:29.636 --> 04:31.304
Hey, can I have
the prize?

04:31.337 --> 04:34.474
My bowl... My prize.

04:34.508 --> 04:35.642
Come on.

04:40.881 --> 04:43.183
(WHISTLING)

04:43.216 --> 04:45.018
Sam, what are you
trying to do, kill me?

04:45.051 --> 04:46.419
Sorry.

04:46.452 --> 04:49.389
Hey, Sammy, what are you
going out as for Halloween?

04:49.422 --> 04:50.924
I‐I'm not going out.

04:50.957 --> 04:52.893
Bill and I are gonna see
The Nude Bomb at Parkway.

04:52.926 --> 04:54.561
Hey, that's a dirty movie.

04:54.595 --> 04:56.162
Dad, it's
a Get Smart movie.

04:56.196 --> 04:59.232
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
You're not going
trick or treating?

04:59.265 --> 05:02.135
Mom! I‐I'm
in ninth grade!

05:02.168 --> 05:04.505
I know.
But you went out last year.

05:04.538 --> 05:07.007
Yeah. Well, last year
I was in junior high.

05:07.040 --> 05:08.441
Yeah, but Sam...

05:08.474 --> 05:10.511
Honey, the boy's 14.

05:10.544 --> 05:12.979
He can miss a night
of walking around
the neighborhood

05:13.013 --> 05:14.247
beggin' like a tramp.

05:14.280 --> 05:16.449
Halloween's for little
kids anyway.

05:17.117 --> 05:18.451
Hey, Lindsay,

05:18.484 --> 05:20.086
you're still gonna hand out
candy with me, aren't you?

05:20.120 --> 05:21.655
Remember how much
fun we had last year

05:21.688 --> 05:24.090
looking at
all the little kids
in their costumes?

05:24.124 --> 05:26.059
Yeah, Mom. I told you
I was going to.

05:26.092 --> 05:27.861
Well, good!

05:27.894 --> 05:30.797
'Cause we're gonna have
a really good time this year,
I promise.

05:36.903 --> 05:38.138
Hey, Lindsay.

05:38.171 --> 05:39.573
Long time no see.

05:39.606 --> 05:41.708
I saw you out here
yesterday.

05:41.742 --> 05:43.744
Why are you
wearing a hat?

05:43.777 --> 05:45.445
It's the day before
Halloween.

05:46.479 --> 05:47.681
That your costume?

05:48.214 --> 05:49.282
It kinda sucks.

05:49.315 --> 05:52.352
No. It's Devil's Day.

05:52.385 --> 05:54.855
Each year, the seniors
bring a hair removal foam

05:54.888 --> 05:56.990
and spray it on
freshmen's heads.

05:57.023 --> 05:58.625
Then all your hair
falls out.

05:58.659 --> 05:59.660
Really?

05:59.693 --> 06:03.396
No. That stupid rumor's
been around for years.

06:03.429 --> 06:05.298
Yeah, I know.
I was just goofin' on 'em.

06:05.331 --> 06:06.933
No, you weren't!

06:06.967 --> 06:08.935
Yes, I was.

06:08.969 --> 06:10.904
Hey, Lindsay.
Hey, Millie.

06:13.640 --> 06:16.309
What are you doing
tomorrow night?

06:16.342 --> 06:17.978
My church is having
a Halloween dance.

06:18.011 --> 06:19.045
You wanna come?

06:19.079 --> 06:21.548
Oh. Well...
I would go,

06:21.582 --> 06:24.217
but I gotta hand out
candy with my mom.

06:24.250 --> 06:26.920
Oh. Okay.

06:30.156 --> 06:31.191
Do you want
some Liqamate?

06:31.224 --> 06:33.727
No. You eat
candy now?

06:33.760 --> 06:35.896
Millie, it's 7:30
in the morning.

06:36.496 --> 06:38.398
It's just Liqamate.

06:38.431 --> 06:40.701
It makes my spit
taste like fruit juice.

06:43.870 --> 06:45.872
DANIEL: Hey, check it out.
It's Lindsay.

06:46.840 --> 06:48.108
Hey, Lindsay.

06:48.141 --> 06:49.442
What's up?

06:49.475 --> 06:50.777
Hey, Daniel.

06:51.778 --> 06:52.813
Hey, Kim.

06:52.846 --> 06:54.548
Hello, Brain.

06:54.581 --> 06:56.883
So, this is your
bus stop?

06:57.450 --> 06:58.785
(KIM GIGGLES)

06:58.819 --> 06:59.820
Yeah.

07:01.154 --> 07:04.691
We've had
the same bus stop
since kindergarten.

07:04.725 --> 07:06.560
How fast does
your car go?

07:07.460 --> 07:10.030
150, if I hook up
the nitrous tank.

07:10.063 --> 07:11.532
(KIM GIGGLES)

07:11.565 --> 07:13.800
Your car
is really loud.

07:13.834 --> 07:15.602
My dad says you
need a muffler.

07:15.636 --> 07:18.905
Once he even threw a rock
at you when you drove by.

07:20.574 --> 07:22.743
But... I guess
you didn't hear it.

07:23.409 --> 07:24.945
He threw a rock
at me?

07:24.978 --> 07:28.081
Hey, kid, what the hell
are you eating?

07:28.114 --> 07:29.583
Is that laundry soap?

07:29.616 --> 07:31.952
It's Liqamate,
want some?

07:31.985 --> 07:33.053
Millie...

07:33.086 --> 07:34.555
U‐um... I'll pass.

07:34.588 --> 07:36.557
Uh, yeah.
We gotta get goin'.

07:37.457 --> 07:38.625
I'd give you
a ride, Linds,

07:38.659 --> 07:41.494
but I got an engine
block in the backseat.

07:43.129 --> 07:44.130
Yeah.

07:46.399 --> 07:47.668
Mmm!

07:49.570 --> 07:50.937
Thanks for the candy, skinny.

07:50.971 --> 07:52.706
(ENGINE ROARS)

07:59.079 --> 08:01.247
See? My dad's right.

08:02.382 --> 08:04.084
He needs a muffler.

08:12.292 --> 08:14.528
GIRL: So are you guys going to
Sara's party tomorrow night?

08:14.561 --> 08:16.730
Yeah, but I think
I'm going to Jim's first.

08:22.869 --> 08:23.970
Hey!

08:24.004 --> 08:27.107
If it isn't the
Amelia Earhart
of McKinley High.

08:27.641 --> 08:29.142
What does that mean?

08:29.175 --> 08:32.378
Well, you head to class,
but you never seem
to get there.

08:32.412 --> 08:36.550
Mr. Rosso, could you not
humiliate me in front of
the whole school?

08:36.583 --> 08:40.220
Come on, Lindsay,
don't turn me into
the man here.

08:40.253 --> 08:41.655
I'm just trying
to help you.

08:41.688 --> 08:44.591
And if, when you
graduate, it turns
out I did help you

08:44.625 --> 08:47.661
but you hate me,
I'm okay with that.

08:47.694 --> 08:48.829
I gotta get to class.

08:48.862 --> 08:50.531
See?
It's workin' already.

08:52.232 --> 08:53.734
Embarrassing.

08:53.767 --> 08:56.469
That's the only word
I can think of

08:56.503 --> 09:02.108
to describe these books
you've chosen to do
your reports on.

09:02.142 --> 09:07.681
<i>Al Jaffe's Snappy Answers</i>
<i>to Stupid Questions.</i>

09:07.714 --> 09:11.652
The novelization
of <i>Star Wars.</i>

09:12.452 --> 09:14.387
<i>Yes I Can,</i>

09:14.420 --> 09:18.224
the autobiography
of Sammy Davis, Jr.

09:21.027 --> 09:24.565
Crime and Punishment
is a good example

09:24.598 --> 09:27.701
of the kind of book
you should be reading now.

09:28.334 --> 09:32.172
In it, Fyodor Dostoevsky

09:32.205 --> 09:34.107
was attempting to create

09:34.140 --> 09:36.076
what some would call

09:36.109 --> 09:38.745
an existential enigma...

09:40.547 --> 09:44.350
A protagonist who was
both a nihilist

09:44.384 --> 09:46.286
and a moralist.

09:47.654 --> 09:49.856
Now, I know this sounds
confusing to you all,

09:49.890 --> 09:53.660
but soon you'll all know
what I'm talking about,

09:53.694 --> 09:55.729
because I expect you to have

09:55.762 --> 09:58.965
the first half of
this book read by Monday.

09:58.999 --> 10:02.102
(CLASS GROANS)
It's time to grow up, people!

10:04.070 --> 10:05.205
You like that?

10:05.238 --> 10:06.507
No!
Gets you hot?

10:06.540 --> 10:08.942
Would you knock it off?
You're making me sick!

10:10.043 --> 10:12.913
Hey... Why don't you
make out with Nicky there,

10:12.946 --> 10:14.447
And we'll call it
a foursome?

10:14.480 --> 10:18.619
Yeah. Why don't you
make out with my butt,
and we'll call it love?

10:18.652 --> 10:19.920
Hey, you guys, be cool.

10:20.486 --> 10:22.055
The narc's here.

10:22.088 --> 10:24.858
Yeah. Watch out,
or I'll bust you.

10:26.359 --> 10:28.629
Hey, man,
I ain't joking.

10:28.662 --> 10:31.632
I heard about
what you did to
Brian Stoker.

10:31.665 --> 10:33.634
Saw him smoking
a "J" outside
the Quick Fill

10:33.667 --> 10:35.736
and went inside
and told some cops?

10:36.803 --> 10:39.105
Brian's in
prison now, man.

10:39.139 --> 10:41.374
And I heard
his brother's
lookin' for you.

10:41.407 --> 10:43.710
What? I didn't do that.

10:48.081 --> 10:49.482
Yeah. I know.

10:49.516 --> 10:52.052
I was just
messing with you.

10:52.085 --> 10:55.488
She got me with
that same joke
last week.

10:55.522 --> 10:57.123
It's kinda funny, though.

10:58.291 --> 11:00.160
Hilarious.

11:00.193 --> 11:02.062
NICK: Hey,
what are you doin'
for Halloween?

11:02.095 --> 11:04.931
Oh, I have to
hand out candy
with my mom.

11:04.965 --> 11:08.134
I know,
it sounds really dorky.

11:09.235 --> 11:10.504
She gets really
into it.

11:10.537 --> 11:11.772
Oh, Lindsay,

11:11.805 --> 11:14.608
I don't think
that sounds
dorky at all.

11:14.641 --> 11:16.643
You know what?
At least she's bein' nice.

11:16.677 --> 11:17.978
Just because you
hate your mother

11:18.011 --> 11:19.980
doesn't mean that
everybody else does, okay?

11:20.013 --> 11:21.782
No, everybody
hates her mother.

11:21.815 --> 11:22.883
(KIM LAUGHING)

11:22.916 --> 11:24.217
Well, what are you
guys doing?

11:24.250 --> 11:27.253
DANIEL: Oh, well, uh, Kim,
Nick and I are goin' out.

11:27.287 --> 11:30.657
Borrow my uncle's
big‐ass Caddy, and...

11:30.691 --> 11:32.358
We thought maybe
you'd like to come with us.

11:33.927 --> 11:36.830
Oh, you mean like
a double date?

11:38.064 --> 11:41.001
If that's what
you need to call it
in your diary, princess.

11:43.269 --> 11:44.270
I can't.

11:45.038 --> 11:46.172
Your loss.

11:46.206 --> 11:48.108
(BELL RINGS)

11:48.141 --> 11:49.375
Oh, the bell.

11:49.409 --> 11:50.877
Let's not be late
for class.

11:50.911 --> 11:53.413
(LAUGHS)
Yeah, right!

11:53.446 --> 11:54.815
Hey, Lindsay,

11:56.449 --> 11:57.984
I... You know,
I think it's...

11:58.018 --> 12:01.087
I think it's nice
that you're helping
your mom hand out candy.

12:02.288 --> 12:04.157
So, I'll see you later.

12:04.190 --> 12:05.191
Yeah.

12:05.792 --> 12:06.993
See you later.

12:11.932 --> 12:14.735
SAM: This is gonna take like
a trillion years to read.

12:14.768 --> 12:16.670
I don't even know
what it's about.

12:16.703 --> 12:18.939
Whitman said it's about
an ax murderer.

12:18.972 --> 12:20.240
BILL: That sounds
kinda cool.

12:20.273 --> 12:22.242
I guarantee you
it's not gonna be cool.

12:22.275 --> 12:25.812
I mean... Look how small
the printing is.

12:25.846 --> 12:27.614
Uh, perhaps
you've never heard

12:27.648 --> 12:29.916
of a little thing called
Cliff Notes?

12:29.950 --> 12:31.985
You still have to
read them.

12:32.018 --> 12:34.855
Whitman is such a jerk!
You know?

12:34.888 --> 12:36.422
She says you have to be
young adults.

12:36.456 --> 12:39.259
We're not adults.
We're kids until
we turn 18.

12:40.561 --> 12:42.696
Maybe you are.
But when I hit 13,

12:42.729 --> 12:44.330
I became a man.

12:44.364 --> 12:47.568
That's only in
your temple, Neal,
not in the real world.

12:47.601 --> 12:51.437
Hey! We should go trick
or treating tomorrow night.

12:51.471 --> 12:54.274
In case you
haven't noticed,
we're a little old.

12:54.307 --> 12:57.043
No, we're not, okay?
We went trick or treating
last year.

12:57.343 --> 12:58.512
Come on.

12:58.545 --> 13:00.313
Let's go out
tomorrow night.

13:00.346 --> 13:03.316
No way. I'm going to
the J. C.'s haunted house.

13:03.349 --> 13:05.085
The Hot dog on a Stick
girls from the mall

13:05.118 --> 13:07.220
are workin' in it.
The tall ones?

13:07.253 --> 13:09.222
Yeah. Judy.

13:09.255 --> 13:10.290
They're hot.

13:10.323 --> 13:11.592
Judy, tootie, tootie!

13:11.625 --> 13:12.959
All right, then
why don't we

13:12.993 --> 13:14.661
go trick or treating
before that?

13:14.695 --> 13:16.563
Why don't we just
go buy candy?

13:16.597 --> 13:18.498
Oh, yeah, that's
really fun.

13:18.532 --> 13:21.401
Come on!
It'll be a blast.

13:21.434 --> 13:22.636
It's better than sitting home

13:22.669 --> 13:24.971
reading some
stupid Russian book.

13:26.139 --> 13:27.273
Sure.

13:27.307 --> 13:28.875
Okay, you know, I...

13:28.909 --> 13:30.376
Yeah, I guess... I could...
You know, we...

13:30.410 --> 13:31.712
I... Yeah, I guess so.

13:31.745 --> 13:33.179
I don't know.

13:33.213 --> 13:35.982
You're never gonna
dress up as Groucho again?

13:38.151 --> 13:39.853
Well... (AS GROUCHO)
That's the most
ridiculous thing

13:39.886 --> 13:41.087
I've ever hoird!

13:42.255 --> 13:43.256
Groucho sucks.

13:54.167 --> 13:55.536
Tommy!

13:55.569 --> 13:56.570
Honey!

14:04.110 --> 14:05.178
Lindsay!

14:12.519 --> 14:13.520
Hey, Lindsay.

14:14.220 --> 14:15.622
What's up?

14:15.656 --> 14:17.490
Millie,
who is that?

14:20.661 --> 14:21.695
Who?

14:21.728 --> 14:23.163
Millie!

14:26.166 --> 14:28.301
You weren't
supposed to see.

14:28.334 --> 14:30.937
That's Tommy,
my secret love.

14:30.971 --> 14:33.106
We met this summer
at church camp.

14:33.974 --> 14:35.942
You have a boyfriend?

14:35.976 --> 14:38.078
Lindsay, you've gotta
keep this a secret.

14:38.111 --> 14:41.715
I mean, Tommy
and I don't even
French kiss yet.

14:41.748 --> 14:43.249
Tommy says
that if you do

14:43.283 --> 14:46.286
before you've been
going out for six months,
you go to hell.

14:47.020 --> 14:49.022
Why didn't you
tell me?

14:49.055 --> 14:51.224
I didn't want to
make you feel bad...

14:51.257 --> 14:53.259
Since you don't
have a boyfriend
and all.

14:59.766 --> 15:01.067
NICK: Come on.
No way!

15:01.101 --> 15:02.503
DANIEL:
I'm telling you, man.
It's true.

15:02.536 --> 15:05.171
When I heard him play
at Cobo Hall,
guy was amazing.

15:05.205 --> 15:09.142
Whoa, hold on a second.
So they're called
Santana, right?

15:09.175 --> 15:12.278
But that guy who's singing...
Is not Santana.

15:12.312 --> 15:15.716
No. Santana's
the guitar player.

15:15.749 --> 15:19.019
Then how did he
get them to name
the band after him?

15:19.052 --> 15:21.021
I don't know, man.

15:21.054 --> 15:22.689
Maybe he's just
a bad ass.

15:24.024 --> 15:26.292
If that's true,
that's amazing.

15:26.326 --> 15:29.262
Hey, maybe we should
name our band Zarios.

15:30.130 --> 15:31.164
Hey!

15:31.197 --> 15:33.399
I'm going out with
you guys tomorrow night.

15:33.433 --> 15:34.568
NICK: Hey!

15:34.601 --> 15:35.769
Hey, that's great!

15:35.802 --> 15:37.638
Yeah, but what
about your mom?

15:37.671 --> 15:40.340
How's she gonna
hand out candy
all by herself?

15:42.408 --> 15:44.545
Well, she'll survive.

15:44.578 --> 15:46.179
DANIEL: Well, well, well...

15:48.615 --> 15:50.751
<i>♪♪ You did the mash</i>

15:50.784 --> 15:52.853
<i>♪♪ You did</i>
<i>the monthster mash</i>

15:52.886 --> 15:55.088
<i>♪♪ It was a smash</i>

15:55.121 --> 15:57.624
<i>♪♪ It was</i>
<i>a graveyard smash ♪♪</i>

15:57.658 --> 15:59.192
Right? (GIGGLES)

16:00.060 --> 16:01.662
SAM: Hey, Mom,

16:01.695 --> 16:03.564
Neal, Bill, and I decided
to go trick or treating
tomorrow night.

16:03.597 --> 16:06.266
Oh, Sam, that's great!
We have to get you a costume.

16:06.299 --> 16:08.969
No, Mom. I'm gonna
make my own.
I'm goin' out as Gort.

16:09.002 --> 16:11.171
He's the robot from
The Day the Earth Stood Still.

16:11.204 --> 16:13.974
Ooh! Gort!
How exciting!

16:14.007 --> 16:17.010
Sam, what are you doing?
You're too old to go out
trick or treating.

16:17.043 --> 16:19.680
Oh, Harold, stop.

16:19.713 --> 16:22.115
Well, it's true!

16:22.148 --> 16:24.751
There was this kid
in my neighborhood
when I was growing up...

16:25.385 --> 16:26.587
Scott Byron.

16:26.620 --> 16:30.657
He kept on trick
or treating until he was
well into his 20s.

16:30.691 --> 16:32.358
You know where
he's living now?

16:32.392 --> 16:35.796
At home.
With his 90‐year‐old mother!

16:35.829 --> 16:37.998
He's the laughing stock
of the community.

16:38.699 --> 16:40.366
Never took a wife, either.

16:40.400 --> 16:41.902
I don't think
there's anything wrong

16:41.935 --> 16:44.805
with acting like a kid
every once in a while.

16:44.838 --> 16:46.372
I know Lindsay and I

16:46.406 --> 16:48.942
are gonna have a great
time tomorrow night,
aren't we, sweetie?

16:48.975 --> 16:50.744
Yeah, Mom. We sure are.

16:51.878 --> 16:53.246
<i>♪♪ He did the mash</i>

16:53.279 --> 16:55.248
<i>♪♪ He did the monthster mash</i>

16:55.281 --> 16:56.883
<i>♪♪ It was a smash</i>

16:56.917 --> 16:59.052
<i>♪♪ It was</i>
<i>a graveyard smash ♪♪</i>

16:59.085 --> 17:01.087
(GIGGLING)

17:03.189 --> 17:04.490
NEAL: Then Bill and I'll
come by your place.

17:04.525 --> 17:06.326
And bring pillow cases.
No grocery bags.

17:06.359 --> 17:07.961
If your bag rips,
you're on your own.

17:07.994 --> 17:09.630
I'm gonna bring
my plastic pumpkin.

17:09.663 --> 17:12.398
Don't bring that.
It gets full
after one street.

17:12.432 --> 17:14.234
Not if I eat the candy
as we go.

17:14.267 --> 17:15.502
Last time
you did that,

17:15.536 --> 17:17.571
you puked before
we got past our bus stop.

17:17.604 --> 17:20.240
Hey, guys. I heard
you were going out for
trick or treats tonight.

17:20.273 --> 17:21.808
How did you
find out about that?

17:21.842 --> 17:23.510
Word gets out.
People talk.

17:23.544 --> 17:25.278
But you gotta be
especially careful,
though.

17:25.311 --> 17:27.380
The Halloween candy's
gonna be really
dangerous this year.

17:27.413 --> 17:29.349
They say that
every year.

17:29.382 --> 17:31.051
Yeah, but this year
there's a bunch of
evil hippies

17:31.084 --> 17:34.054
who don't want Reagan
to be president, so to
disrupt the election,

17:34.087 --> 17:36.690
they're going to inject
the candy with heroin
and turn kids into addicts.

17:36.723 --> 17:40.026
That's not true.
You just have to watch out
for pins and razor blades.

17:40.060 --> 17:42.529
Yeah, and rat hair's
a big one.

17:42.563 --> 17:44.798
You're gonna
find yourself wishing
for rat hair.

17:44.831 --> 17:47.200
Word on the street
is they're putting
a poo in fun‐sized

17:47.233 --> 17:48.902
candy bar wrappers
and handing those out.

17:48.935 --> 17:51.572
I love fun‐sized
candy bars.

17:51.605 --> 17:52.739
Oh, that's stupid.

17:52.773 --> 17:55.141
Like nobody'd
be able to tell
what it really was.

17:55.175 --> 17:56.543
They dip it in
chocolate first

17:56.577 --> 17:58.144
so you can't
tell the difference
until it's too late.

18:00.046 --> 18:01.247
See ya.

18:04.751 --> 18:05.986
Actually, it sounds kinda fun.

18:06.019 --> 18:07.453
You mind if I come
with you guys?

18:10.857 --> 18:12.025
Mom?

18:12.058 --> 18:14.494
JEAN: In the kitchen!

18:21.067 --> 18:23.737
Hey, Lindsay,
where have you been?

18:23.770 --> 18:25.606
You're gonna miss
the first trick or treaters.

18:25.639 --> 18:28.241
You know
the cutest ones
always come early.

18:28.274 --> 18:30.443
Yeah. Well,
I was hanging out
with my friends.

18:30.476 --> 18:31.612
Lindsay...

18:31.645 --> 18:32.713
Lo...ah! Ow.

18:32.746 --> 18:34.781
Look at what
we're gonna hand
out this year.

18:34.815 --> 18:37.317
Halloween cookies!
(GIGGLES)

18:38.018 --> 18:39.119
That's great, Mom.

18:39.152 --> 18:40.486
SAM: What's up with
all the cookies?

18:40.521 --> 18:43.256
Sam, I laid your
robot costume out
on your bed.

18:43.289 --> 18:44.691
You didn't rip it,
did you?

18:44.725 --> 18:47.628
No. But I wrote,
"My son's the cutest boy
in the whole world"

18:47.661 --> 18:49.329
on the front of it.

18:49.362 --> 18:52.132
Lindsay, I got you a costume.
Go put it on, sweetie.

18:52.165 --> 18:55.268
I'm gonna put these
cookies by the door.

18:55.301 --> 18:58.905
We are gonna have
so much fun!

19:04.077 --> 19:06.580
Kinda hate when Mom
gets goofy like that.

19:29.402 --> 19:30.837
Mmm.

19:30.871 --> 19:32.839
Lookin' for Chaplin...

19:32.873 --> 19:34.575
I'm only seeing Hitler.

19:38.111 --> 19:39.813
If I were
The Bionic Woman,

19:40.380 --> 19:41.815
what would I wear?

20:04.705 --> 20:06.172
This is ridiculous.

20:06.206 --> 20:07.774
I look like Tom Selleck!

20:07.808 --> 20:09.009
<i>♪♪ Gonna raise hell</i>

20:09.042 --> 20:10.343
Mom!

20:11.477 --> 20:14.681
<i>♪♪ Gonna raise hell</i>

20:15.849 --> 20:19.219
<i>♪♪ Gonna raise hell ♪♪</i>

20:19.252 --> 20:22.488
I'm sorry, Steve Austin.
I can't marry you.

20:22.523 --> 20:24.691
I'm mad at you right now.

20:25.058 --> 20:26.292
What?

20:26.326 --> 20:27.994
I'm sorry,
I can't hear you.

20:28.028 --> 20:30.764
Hold on. I'm gonna put
the phone on my bionic ear.

20:34.300 --> 20:36.469
That's... That's better.

20:37.370 --> 20:40.073
No, don't talk so loud!

20:40.106 --> 20:42.275
Don't forget,
I've got bionic hearing.

20:43.009 --> 20:45.879
No, these are not bionic.

20:45.912 --> 20:47.648
These are all me.

20:51.384 --> 20:53.787
I heard that
crack, pal.

20:53.820 --> 20:55.255
Oh... Oh, it wasn't you.

20:55.288 --> 20:57.190
Oh, okay,
I guess I'll just...

20:57.223 --> 20:59.259
(MAKING BIONIC SOUND)
Do‐do‐do‐do‐do‐do...

20:59.292 --> 21:01.928
Oscar Goldman,
it's me, Jaime Sommers.

21:01.962 --> 21:04.798
Steve Austin is trapped
in the... In the reacting...

21:06.466 --> 21:09.469
Hi, Mom. Okay.
You can use the phone.

21:10.136 --> 21:11.938
(DOORBELL RINGS)

21:11.972 --> 21:13.974
Oh. Hey, Lindsay,

21:14.007 --> 21:15.275
Hurry up, honey.

21:15.308 --> 21:17.443
Our first little
visitors are here!

21:18.144 --> 21:19.880
Linds?

21:19.913 --> 21:21.715
Oh! Oh... Ha!

21:21.748 --> 21:23.016
Oh, my...

21:23.049 --> 21:25.619
What an interesting
costume.

21:25.652 --> 21:26.753
Oh, wa...

21:27.654 --> 21:28.488
Here you go.

21:28.522 --> 21:30.591
All right.
Happy Halloween.

21:33.760 --> 21:35.662
Do you... Do you want
another cookie?

21:36.830 --> 21:37.864
Okay.

21:39.265 --> 21:40.466
I'm, uh...
I'm here to go out

21:40.500 --> 21:42.002
for trick or treats
tonight with Sam.

21:42.035 --> 21:43.604
Oh, you're one of
Sam's frien...

21:43.637 --> 21:46.039
I am so sorry.
Come on in.

21:46.773 --> 21:47.874
My gosh!

21:48.308 --> 21:49.643
Sorry.

21:51.545 --> 21:53.146
Nice costume.
You look like

21:53.179 --> 21:54.648
Richard Benjamin
in <i>Westworld.</i>

21:57.984 --> 22:00.320
Say, don't you
look nice?

22:02.789 --> 22:05.158
What in the hell
are you supposed to be?

22:05.191 --> 22:06.727
I'm a guy with a knife
through his head.

22:06.760 --> 22:08.294
Oh. Well...

22:08.328 --> 22:09.362
Mission accomplished.

22:09.395 --> 22:11.164
Hey, Mom!

22:11.197 --> 22:12.799
Mom, I gotta talk to you.
(DOORBELL RINGS)

22:12.833 --> 22:16.503
Get your costume on, honey.
The trick or treaters
are here! Oh!

22:16.537 --> 22:19.172
BOTH: Trick or treat,
smell our feet,

22:19.205 --> 22:21.675
give us something
good to eat.

22:21.708 --> 22:22.876
If you...

22:22.909 --> 22:24.077
(LAUGHING)

22:24.110 --> 22:25.579
You guys are
both great.

22:25.612 --> 22:27.914
Come on in!
Get in here!

22:27.948 --> 22:29.415
(LAUGHING)

22:31.618 --> 22:34.054
Wow. Harris,
that looks really real.

22:34.087 --> 22:35.556
How do you know
it isn't?

22:37.558 --> 22:38.992
Oh!
If I held you any closer,

22:39.025 --> 22:40.093
I'd be in back of ya.

22:40.126 --> 22:41.562
Hey, cut that out!

22:41.595 --> 22:44.464
You know, Bill,
you look really lovely.

22:44.497 --> 22:46.633
I'm Jaime Sommers,
The Bionic Woman.

22:46.667 --> 22:48.869
Oh, of course
you are!

22:48.902 --> 22:50.203
(WHEELS SCREECH)

22:50.236 --> 22:51.371
What was that?

22:51.404 --> 22:52.539
(HORN HONKS)

22:52.573 --> 22:54.841
Mom... I'm gonna
go hang out with

22:54.875 --> 22:56.376
my friends
a little bit, okay?
I'll be back.

22:56.409 --> 22:58.178
Wait, Lindsay...
Mom, I'll be back!

22:58.211 --> 22:59.780
Sweetie, wait!

22:59.813 --> 23:01.548
DANIEL: Come on, Lindsay.
Let's go.

23:04.317 --> 23:05.886
You have any fake blood
around here?

23:05.919 --> 23:08.421
I wanna freshen up
my wound before
we go out.

23:09.189 --> 23:10.390
What?

23:22.903 --> 23:24.070
She did what?

23:24.104 --> 23:26.272
She said it
was only gonna be
for a little while.

23:26.306 --> 23:27.641
She'll be back.

23:27.674 --> 23:30.010
You know, she was
really looking
forward to this.

23:30.043 --> 23:32.646
Yeah. Well,
she better be back.
That's all I can say.

23:32.679 --> 23:34.715
That daughter
of yours is
on thin ice.

23:34.748 --> 23:36.683
Until she gets back,
would you put this on

23:36.717 --> 23:38.885
and help me
pass out cookies.

23:42.055 --> 23:44.525
Oh, for crying
out loud.

23:44.925 --> 23:47.027
Whoa‐oh‐oh‐oh!

23:47.060 --> 23:48.061
Don't fall out.

23:52.799 --> 23:53.834
Boo.

23:56.436 --> 23:58.471
His plans
fell through.

23:59.039 --> 24:00.240
You know?

24:00.273 --> 24:02.008
I'm sorry.

24:02.042 --> 24:04.244
♪♪ She's a roller

24:04.277 --> 24:06.279
♪♪ A high‐roller baby ♪♪

24:06.312 --> 24:07.480
Knock it off, blondie.

24:07.514 --> 24:09.149
You're gonna
blow the speakers.

24:09.182 --> 24:10.416
Oh, I'm sorry, Grandpa.

24:10.450 --> 24:12.686
I'll try not to blow
anything of yours
from now on.

24:14.821 --> 24:18.024
Hey! What
are we gonna do?

24:18.058 --> 24:20.661
There's this haunted house
that's supposed to be
really scary.

24:20.694 --> 24:22.829
Yeah. Hey, dude.
That could be
kind of fun, right?

24:22.863 --> 24:23.964
For who, losers?

24:23.997 --> 24:27.534
Hey, shut up.
I like haunted houses.

24:27.568 --> 24:29.803
(LAUGHING)
I rest my case.

24:29.836 --> 24:33.306
DANIEL: Oh, listen.
Can't we just drive around,

24:33.339 --> 24:35.241
see where the
night takes us.

24:35.275 --> 24:36.777
Is that cool
with you?

24:37.310 --> 24:38.779
Lindsay?

24:38.812 --> 24:39.913
Yeah.

24:41.481 --> 24:43.149
I'm up for anything.

24:43.183 --> 24:44.518
DANIEL:
Right on, kid.

24:46.486 --> 24:48.655
Hey, I'm really glad
that you decided to come.

24:49.255 --> 24:50.490
Thanks.

24:51.324 --> 24:52.559
So am I.

24:55.428 --> 24:57.698
You two
are adorable.

25:00.266 --> 25:01.301
Mom, look.

25:01.334 --> 25:02.869
Jessica, come on.
Don't stare.

25:02.903 --> 25:03.937
It's not polite.

25:08.341 --> 25:10.877
Why is everybody
staring at me?

25:10.911 --> 25:13.814
I mean, you'd
think they never saw
The Bionic Woman before.

25:13.847 --> 25:16.983
They just probably
didn't know she was
so hot in real life.

25:17.017 --> 25:17.851
(LAUGHING)

25:17.884 --> 25:20.086
You... Are you...
Are you joking?

25:20.120 --> 25:21.221
You're joking, right?

25:21.254 --> 25:23.524
I saw the real
Jaime Sommers at
the Auto Show last year.

25:23.557 --> 25:24.891
Her boobs
weren't that big.

25:24.925 --> 25:27.127
Hey, we should
go to the rich
neighborhood first.

25:27.160 --> 25:29.129
They hand out
the best candy.

25:29.162 --> 25:30.263
It's not true.

25:30.296 --> 25:32.298
Rich people
traditionally give out
the cheapest candy.

25:32.332 --> 25:34.134
It's how
they stay rich.

25:34.167 --> 25:36.670
BILL: I just hope
I get some candy
I can eat.

25:36.703 --> 25:39.540
Yeah, I'm allergic to peanuts,
licorice and nougat.

25:39.573 --> 25:42.175
How can you possibly
be allergic to nougat?

25:42.208 --> 25:43.910
(LAUGHING)
I don't know.

25:43.944 --> 25:46.412
Uh, my doctor
says I'm allergic
to more things

25:46.446 --> 25:48.982
than anyone
he's ever seen.

25:49.015 --> 25:51.718
Then I got dibs on
all your malt balls.

25:51.752 --> 25:55.188
You can have 'em.
I like pixie sticks.

25:55.221 --> 25:56.289
Pixie sticks rule.

25:56.322 --> 25:58.191
No way.
Chunkies are the best.

25:58.224 --> 26:00.160
Uh‐uh. Candy corn,
my friend.

26:00.193 --> 26:03.129
I must admit, I'm
a wax lips man myself.

26:04.397 --> 26:06.299
KIDS: Trick or treat!

26:06.332 --> 26:07.701
Why, you're
the cutest things.

26:07.734 --> 26:09.135
Hey, Harold,
come look!

26:09.169 --> 26:10.303
Aah!

26:10.336 --> 26:12.639
KIDS: Aah!

26:13.406 --> 26:15.542
Oh, kids! I was
just kidding!

26:15.576 --> 26:17.277
I'm not really
a vampire.

26:17.310 --> 26:18.712
I own a sporting
goods store.

26:18.745 --> 26:21.347
Hey? What's
the big idea,
scaring my kids?

26:21.381 --> 26:22.683
I... I didn't mean to.

26:22.716 --> 26:25.351
No, I... I'm sorry.
I made him put this on.

26:25.385 --> 26:28.221
Here. Give these
to your children.
They're homemade.

26:28.254 --> 26:29.656
Are you crazy?

26:29.690 --> 26:31.257
I've been lecturing
my kids for weeks

26:31.291 --> 26:33.126
not to take
unwrapped candy.

26:33.159 --> 26:35.862
Those cookies could
have razor blades
or pins in them.

26:35.896 --> 26:37.631
I... I wouldn't
do that.

26:49.743 --> 26:51.277
Come on, cowgirl.

26:51.311 --> 26:53.580
Enough of this
kid's stuff.

26:53.614 --> 26:54.881
Let's head out
to the barn,

26:54.915 --> 26:57.217
and I'll give you
a real good roll
in the hay.

26:57.250 --> 26:59.019
Oh, Harold,
not now.

27:03.023 --> 27:04.024
When?

27:04.725 --> 27:06.326
I mean,
think about it.

27:06.359 --> 27:09.930
All the people
in this town
are real religious.

27:09.963 --> 27:11.431
But just 'cause
it's Halloween,

27:11.464 --> 27:14.200
they'll hang
pictures of devils,
witches, ghosts

27:14.234 --> 27:15.969
all over their houses.

27:16.002 --> 27:17.070
It's a joke.

27:17.103 --> 27:18.038
Yeah. Yeah, I know.

27:18.071 --> 27:20.907
It's total white,
middle‐class hypocrisy.

27:20.941 --> 27:23.143
Yeah. Right.
Exactly.

27:23.176 --> 27:25.311
You wanna know what
I think about it?

27:25.345 --> 27:26.412
(BURPS)

27:27.814 --> 27:29.683
KEN: That's lovely,
you know. Your years

27:29.716 --> 27:32.152
in charm school
really paid off.

27:32.185 --> 27:34.655
By the way, how are
things going at ass school?

27:35.121 --> 27:36.657
Getting all As.

27:36.957 --> 27:38.358
Ohh.

27:38.391 --> 27:39.660
Hey, you know
where we could go?

27:39.693 --> 27:40.794
We could go
to the movies.

27:40.827 --> 27:42.395
There's a new
Friday the 13th playing.

27:42.428 --> 27:44.264
God, Brain! Why are
you so hung up

27:44.297 --> 27:45.632
about doing
something?

27:45.666 --> 27:46.833
What? Are we
boring to you?

27:46.867 --> 27:48.401
What are you
talking about?

27:48.434 --> 27:49.636
We should do
something.

27:49.670 --> 27:51.004
We can't just
drive around
all night, man.

27:51.037 --> 27:52.939
Hey, man, we
ain't gonna just
drive around.

27:53.439 --> 27:54.708
It's Halloween.

27:55.576 --> 27:57.010
We are...

27:57.043 --> 28:00.380
<i>♪♪ Gonna raise hell,</i>
<i>gonna raise hell</i>

28:00.413 --> 28:03.183
<i>♪♪ Gonna raise hell ♪♪</i>

28:09.790 --> 28:11.224
(DOORBELL BUZZES)

28:11.257 --> 28:13.059
TOGETHER:
Trick or treat!

28:14.260 --> 28:15.729
Okay... Yeah.

28:17.798 --> 28:18.899
What do you want?

28:18.932 --> 28:21.301
Uh...
Trick or treat.

28:22.268 --> 28:24.437
Aren't you guys
a little old for this?

28:25.739 --> 28:27.473
We're only
freshmen in
high school.

28:27.508 --> 28:28.542
High school?

28:28.575 --> 28:30.176
That's too old.

28:31.377 --> 28:32.879
We're young
at heart.

28:36.416 --> 28:37.584
Ooh, circus peanuts.

28:37.618 --> 28:39.720
What the hell are
you supposed to be
anyway? Tin Man?

28:39.753 --> 28:41.622
I'm... I'm Gort.
He's the robot

28:41.655 --> 28:43.223
from <i>The Day</i>
<i>the Earth Stood Still.</i>

28:44.290 --> 28:47.193
You look like
the fricking Tin Man.

28:47.227 --> 28:49.162
BILL: Um, ma'am...

28:49.195 --> 28:51.698
I hope there
aren't any peanuts
in these peanuts.

28:51.732 --> 28:54.134
'Cause if there are,
I could d‐die.

28:54.601 --> 28:55.936
Good night.

28:59.339 --> 29:01.041
WOMAN:
These are so cute.

29:01.074 --> 29:03.143
But, you know, Jean,
they train the kids

29:03.176 --> 29:06.412
not to take
unwrapped foodstuffs.

29:06.446 --> 29:07.748
You should see
all the parents

29:07.781 --> 29:09.750
who are dumping
the cookies on your lawn.

29:09.783 --> 29:11.618
They're all
covered with ants.

29:11.652 --> 29:12.886
What?

29:13.820 --> 29:16.256
Well, happy Halloween.

29:21.728 --> 29:22.963
I give up.

29:24.931 --> 29:27.901
Harold, run up
to Farmer Jack
and buy some candy.

29:27.934 --> 29:30.036
What? Dressed
like this?

29:34.107 --> 29:35.408
All right.

29:35.441 --> 29:37.443
Don't answer
the door till
I get back.

29:39.445 --> 29:41.047
Stupid kids' holiday.

29:43.684 --> 29:47.521
I say we make
Lindsay do it.

29:47.554 --> 29:50.090
DANIEL: No.
I'm going in.

29:50.123 --> 29:52.492
Hey, no, no, man.
Let me do it, all right?

29:53.126 --> 29:54.194
Okay.

30:06.907 --> 30:08.108
DANIEL: Hey, relax.

30:08.141 --> 30:10.443
It's Halloween.
We're supposed
to do this stuff.

30:19.520 --> 30:20.521
DANIEL: Whoa!

30:22.556 --> 30:23.924
Whoa!

30:32.132 --> 30:35.902
Oh, man.
That is so uncool.

30:45.045 --> 30:48.114
I can't believe
we just did that.

30:48.148 --> 30:52.285
Yes, congratulations
to us all, indeed.

30:52.318 --> 30:55.989
I'm so happy I'm not
at the Ted Nugent concert.

31:00.794 --> 31:01.862
Go.

31:01.895 --> 31:03.530
Go ahead, Linds.

31:03.564 --> 31:05.231
Go.
DANIEL: You can do it.

31:19.580 --> 31:21.047
Oh, my...

31:28.689 --> 31:30.023
KEN: Oh, my God.

31:30.056 --> 31:32.526
Come on!
Come on, Lindsay!

31:47.508 --> 31:48.542
Happy Halloween.

31:49.743 --> 31:50.911
This one's for you.

31:50.944 --> 31:52.579
HARRIS: Oh, look.
It's fun‐sized.

31:56.049 --> 31:57.684
You guys having
a good time?

31:58.418 --> 31:59.419
Yeah.

32:00.754 --> 32:02.088
Happy Halloween.

32:03.957 --> 32:05.391
Um... Thank you.

32:05.425 --> 32:07.961
Uh... I'll eat it...
I'll eat it later.

32:13.534 --> 32:15.636
Whoa! Whoa!

32:30.917 --> 32:33.153
Batter up, baby!

32:34.788 --> 32:36.456
Mail's in, baby!

32:50.637 --> 32:51.672
All right.
There it is.

32:51.705 --> 32:52.739
Go for it, Weir.

32:52.773 --> 32:54.474
Do it already.

32:54.508 --> 32:55.976
Okay, okay.

33:01.114 --> 33:03.349
Whoa! (LAUGHS)

33:11.357 --> 33:12.726
(LAUGHING)

33:16.196 --> 33:18.832
Great.
Thanks a lot.

33:18.865 --> 33:21.635
I can't believe this.

33:21.668 --> 33:24.437
I can't believe
the Hot Dog on a Stick
girls saw us.

33:24.470 --> 33:26.472
That's months
of groundwork
down the drain.

33:26.507 --> 33:28.108
Like they'd ever
go out with you.

33:28.141 --> 33:29.375
Hey, shut up.
They like me.

33:29.409 --> 33:31.712
They always give me
free lemonade refills.

33:32.646 --> 33:34.314
ALAN: Well, well, well.

33:34.347 --> 33:36.416
If it isn't the geek patrol.

33:37.551 --> 33:40.120
Oh, no, no,
no, no.

33:41.487 --> 33:43.223
Oh, my God.

33:43.256 --> 33:45.692
Hey, Alan.
What's up?

33:45.726 --> 33:48.161
I don't know whose ass
I want to kick first.

33:48.194 --> 33:49.663
You better
watch out, Alan.

33:49.696 --> 33:50.831
We kicked your ass once.

33:50.864 --> 33:52.232
We'll kick it again.

33:52.265 --> 33:55.101
I don't think so.
That was three
against one.

33:55.135 --> 33:57.103
Now we got us
a fair fight.

33:57.137 --> 33:59.139
It's time
to settle the score.

34:00.006 --> 34:03.009
DANIEL: Oh, yeah.
(LAUGHING)

34:03.043 --> 34:04.244
No, no, no.
I got it. I got it.

34:04.277 --> 34:05.879
Let's go soap
the school's windows.

34:05.912 --> 34:10.517
No, look. I say
it's time we get down
to some serious damage.

34:10.551 --> 34:11.652
Kenneth?

34:14.120 --> 34:15.321
Breakfast, anyone?

34:15.889 --> 34:17.357
NICK: Oh, my goodness.

34:17.390 --> 34:19.626
We don't want
to fight you, Alan.

34:19.660 --> 34:21.361
ALAN: You don't have to.

34:21.394 --> 34:23.597
Just give us your candy
and you're free to go.

34:23.630 --> 34:25.131
Okay, here.

34:28.735 --> 34:29.770
ALAN: Now you, dork.

34:29.803 --> 34:30.837
Forget it.

34:30.871 --> 34:32.305
We went through
a lot for this.

34:32.338 --> 34:34.007
Shut your mouth,
you little girl.

34:34.040 --> 34:36.543
I'm not a little girl.
I'm a Bionic Woman.

34:36.577 --> 34:37.778
Yeah? Prove it.

34:42.883 --> 34:44.718
NEAL: No,
cut it out. Stop.

34:44.751 --> 34:46.987
Just take the candy.
This is my grandpa's coat.

34:47.020 --> 34:48.254
(CLOTH RIPS)

34:48.288 --> 34:51.291
Ow. Fell on my knife.

34:51.324 --> 34:52.759
Come on, let's get
out of here.

34:58.899 --> 35:01.301
NEAL: That's it.
That is it.

35:01.868 --> 35:04.204
This is all your fault.

35:04.237 --> 35:07.040
I never should have
let you talk me into this.

35:07.073 --> 35:09.610
I didn't talk you
into anything.

35:09.643 --> 35:12.345
Oh, well, it sure
as hell wasn't my idea.

35:14.280 --> 35:16.049
Oh, yeah.
You're too cool

35:16.082 --> 35:17.584
getting free
lemonade refills.

35:17.618 --> 35:20.521
BILL: Guys! Let's just
stick to the plan.

35:21.421 --> 35:22.823
This thing on straight?

35:25.659 --> 35:26.793
Know how
to throw it?

35:26.827 --> 35:28.695
Dig in, children.
Awesome.

35:29.663 --> 35:31.231
Thank you.

35:31.264 --> 35:32.999
All right, jackpot.
Jackpot. Come on.

35:33.033 --> 35:34.300
All right. Where?

35:34.334 --> 35:35.936
KIM: Ready? Over there!
Where?

35:35.969 --> 35:38.204
You're such a baby.
Have to have your
little baby's evening.

35:38.238 --> 35:41.642
Yeah, going to some stupid
haunted house is much better.
Yeah, you're stupid.

35:41.675 --> 35:43.844
Takes one to know one.
Well, you are one.

35:43.877 --> 35:45.546
Enough, guys.
Come on.

35:45.579 --> 35:48.014
My bra's chafing.
Let's get home.

35:48.048 --> 35:49.516
LINDSAY: Where?
I can't see.

35:49.550 --> 35:51.317
Kim, you're
blocking my view.

35:51.718 --> 35:52.786
Now!

35:55.989 --> 35:58.224
(CHEERING)

35:58.258 --> 36:00.026
Awesome, man.
That was so awesome.

36:00.060 --> 36:01.795
DANIEL: Nailed 'em,
baby, nailed 'em.

36:01.828 --> 36:02.863
That was amazing.
What?

36:02.896 --> 36:04.565
Oh, my God.
What?

36:04.598 --> 36:06.800
We just egged
my little brother.

36:12.038 --> 36:13.439
Oh, my God.

36:14.808 --> 36:16.543
Wait, stop the car.

36:16.577 --> 36:18.044
It's just eggs.
He'll be fine.

36:18.078 --> 36:20.113
No, stop the car.
Please, Daniel.

36:20.146 --> 36:22.983
Just take it easy.
Take it easy.

36:23.016 --> 36:24.350
Let me
out of the car!

36:24.384 --> 36:25.852
Hey, Daniel, stop
the car, all right?

36:25.886 --> 36:27.187
Just stop the car.
Let her out.

36:27.220 --> 36:29.556
Don't get out.
We'll get him.

36:30.991 --> 36:32.258
LINDSAY: Sam?

36:33.727 --> 36:34.828
Gentlemen...

36:35.328 --> 36:36.730
I'm going home.

36:42.335 --> 36:44.304
Oh, my God.
They're coming back
to finish us off.

36:44.337 --> 36:46.740
Run for it!
Let's go cut through
their back yard!

36:50.744 --> 36:51.778
Sam?

36:53.346 --> 36:55.248
Sam, I'm sorry.

36:55.281 --> 36:56.783
Look, get in the car.

36:58.752 --> 37:01.688
Sam, I'm really sorry.
Please? Come on.

37:01.722 --> 37:03.790
Let us give you
a ride home, okay?

37:06.593 --> 37:09.229
DANIEL: Kid. It's not
your sister's fault.

37:09.262 --> 37:10.764
She didn't even
know it was you.

37:10.797 --> 37:13.266
Look, she's really,
really upset, kid.

37:13.299 --> 37:14.635
I swear to God.

37:14.668 --> 37:16.870
It's true, Sam.
I swear to God.

37:19.139 --> 37:20.340
Sam!

37:20.674 --> 37:21.742
Sam!

37:22.909 --> 37:24.645
God.

37:24.678 --> 37:27.914
Is it just me,
or did he seem upset?

37:27.948 --> 37:29.149
Would you
shut up, please?

37:29.182 --> 37:30.617
(LAUGHING)

37:30.651 --> 37:33.186
Just give her
a break, all right?

37:33.219 --> 37:35.388
Man, I am in
so much trouble.

37:35.421 --> 37:36.657
Just take me home.

37:36.690 --> 37:38.158
No, hey, why don't you
just stick around...

37:38.191 --> 37:40.927
Just take her home,
already. God.

37:40.961 --> 37:42.763
I told you
she'd be a drag.

38:24.838 --> 38:26.039
(DOORBELL RINGS)

38:26.072 --> 38:27.974
KIDS: Trick or treat!

38:33.213 --> 38:34.447
(DOOR OPENS)

38:35.281 --> 38:38.051
Oh, my God.
Sam, what happened!

38:38.084 --> 38:39.252
I got egged.

38:39.285 --> 38:40.353
What's the matter?
What's going on?

38:40.386 --> 38:41.588
Sam got attacked.
Are you all right?

38:41.622 --> 38:42.989
Did you get egg
in your eyes?

38:43.023 --> 38:44.057
I'm fine.

38:44.090 --> 38:45.358
Oh, my God.

38:46.593 --> 38:48.328
HAROLD: Well, well, well.
Look who's here.

38:48.361 --> 38:51.164
So happy you could
grace us with your presence.

38:51.197 --> 38:52.666
JEAN: What kind of
terrible people

38:52.699 --> 38:55.268
would do this
to a little boy?

38:55.301 --> 38:56.970
Who the hell did
this to you, Sam?

39:00.306 --> 39:01.708
Some freaks.

39:01.742 --> 39:05.245
Freaks? Like
circus freaks?

39:05.278 --> 39:06.980
Jean, I don't think
there's bearded ladies

39:07.013 --> 39:10.416
running around
throwing eggs at kids.
He means hippies.

39:10.450 --> 39:12.052
HAROLD: You know who
these freaks were?

39:13.453 --> 39:15.288
Just a bunch
of dirtbags.

39:15.321 --> 39:17.891
Oh, honey.
My little baby boy.

39:17.924 --> 39:19.425
I'm not a baby.

39:24.665 --> 39:28.101
Certainly glad
we all decided to
celebrate Halloween.

39:28.134 --> 39:29.536
Last time I had
this much fun

39:29.570 --> 39:32.573
I was pinned
down in a foxhole
by the North Koreans.

39:36.209 --> 39:37.511
I'm sorry, hon.

39:37.544 --> 39:38.979
You did a nice job.

39:44.150 --> 39:47.754
And you are
on thin ice, missy.

39:49.790 --> 39:52.926
Whew. I didn't
expect you back so soon.

39:54.027 --> 39:56.296
Mom, I told you
I'd be back
in a little bit.

39:56.329 --> 39:58.565
Who were those people
you went off with?

39:58.599 --> 39:59.966
Just some friends
from school.

40:00.000 --> 40:01.234
Anyone I know?

40:01.267 --> 40:02.636
Uh‐uh.
Not really.

40:04.170 --> 40:07.708
Lindsay, if you
didn't want to hand
out candy with me,

40:07.741 --> 40:09.275
you could have
just told me.

40:09.309 --> 40:10.544
I couldn't...

40:10.577 --> 40:13.013
Mom, I didn't
want to make
you feel bad.

40:15.849 --> 40:17.551
Oh, I don't know.

40:19.219 --> 40:20.754
(SIGHS)

40:20.787 --> 40:23.256
The world is such
a different place

40:23.289 --> 40:25.158
than the one
I grew up in.

40:26.593 --> 40:32.132
Everyone just seems
so much meaner these days.

40:32.165 --> 40:35.035
Mom, kids didn't
throw eggs when
you were in school?

40:36.269 --> 40:38.004
I don't know.
I guess so.

40:40.574 --> 40:42.576
I just know
I never did.

40:55.956 --> 40:56.957
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

40:57.524 --> 40:58.792
(DOOR OPENS)

41:03.029 --> 41:04.430
Nothing like getting
yelled at by Dad

41:04.464 --> 41:06.132
when he's dressed
like a vampire, huh?

41:12.338 --> 41:13.707
Thanks for not
turning me in.

41:18.845 --> 41:21.081
I'm really sorry.
You know that,
don't you?

41:25.652 --> 41:27.554
Nobody thinks
you're cool, you know.

41:31.357 --> 41:32.693
Trust me. I know.

42:00.020 --> 42:02.756
(DOORBELL RINGS)
KIDS: Trick or treat!

42:09.630 --> 42:11.231
LINDSAY: Mom?

42:11.264 --> 42:14.267
Oh, no.
(LAUGHING)

42:14.300 --> 42:15.969
That's the wrong costume.

42:18.171 --> 42:20.907
You were supposed
to be my little princess.

42:22.609 --> 42:24.711
Well, I guess
I'll have to be

42:24.745 --> 42:26.880
your little
prince instead.

42:33.486 --> 42:34.721
(DOORBELL RINGS)

42:34.755 --> 42:36.156
I'll get it.
Ohh.

42:37.157 --> 42:39.325
KIDS: Trick or treat!

42:39.359 --> 42:41.327
Aren't you
the cutest things?

42:41.361 --> 42:43.463
Lindsay, aren't they cute?

42:43.496 --> 42:45.699
Yeah. They are.

42:49.035 --> 42:50.270
Here you go.

42:52.172 --> 42:53.774
Happy Halloween.

43:02.549 --> 43:03.950
Sam?

43:03.984 --> 43:05.051
Can I come in?

43:05.085 --> 43:06.086
Yeah.

43:08.955 --> 43:09.956
You okay?

43:10.991 --> 43:13.326
Yeah. I'm just reading
a book for school.

43:15.095 --> 43:16.096
Is it any good?

43:17.197 --> 43:18.098
I don't know yet.

43:18.131 --> 43:20.667
Everyone's name is
really weird and long.

43:22.068 --> 43:24.170
Well, don't stay up
too late.

43:25.338 --> 43:26.607
I won't, Dad.
